1. Total relaxation-rate tensor via Matthiessenâ€™s rule:  
$$
(\tau_{\rm tot})^{-1}_{ij}
=(\tau^{(P)})^{-1}_{ij}+(\tau^{(I)})^{-1}_{ij}
=\begin{pmatrix}
\frac1{\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}}+\frac1{\tau^{(I)}} & 0 & 0\\
0 & \frac1{\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}}+\frac1{\tau^{(I)}} & 0\\
0 & 0 & \frac1{\tau^{(I)}}
\end{pmatrix}.
$$

2. Conductivity and resistivity tensors:  
$$
\sigma_{ij}=C\,\tau_{{\rm tot},\,ij}, 
\quad 
\eta_{ij}=(\sigma^{-1})_{ij}=\frac1C(\tau_{\rm tot}^{-1})_{ij}.
$$

3. Ohmic decay rate for a Fourier mode $\mathbf B\propto e^{i\mathbf k\cdot\mathbf r}e^{-t/\mathcal T}$:  
$$
\frac1{\mathcal T}=\frac1{\mu_0}\,k_i\,\eta_{ij}\,k_j.
$$

4. For $\mathbf k$ purely perpendicular ($k_x=k$, $k_y=k_z=0$):  
$$
\frac1{\mathcal T_\perp}
=\frac{k^2}{\mu_0}\,\eta_{xx}
=\frac{k^2}{\mu_0C}\Bigl(\frac1{\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}}+\frac1{\tau^{(I)}}\Bigr).
$$

5. For $\mathbf k$ purely parallel ($k_z=k$, $k_x=k_y=0$):  
$$
\frac1{\mathcal T_\parallel}
=\frac{k^2}{\mu_0}\,\eta_{zz}
=\frac{k^2}{\mu_0C}\,\frac1{\tau^{(I)}}.
$$

6. Ratio of timescales:
$$
\frac{\mathcal T_\perp}{\mathcal T_\parallel}
=\frac{1/\mathcal T_\parallel}{1/\mathcal T_\perp}
=\frac{\displaystyle\frac1{\tau^{(I)}}}
{\displaystyle\frac1{\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}}+\frac1{\tau^{(I)}}}
=\frac1{1+\frac{\tau^{(I)}}{\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}}}
=\frac1{1+\alpha}\,,
$$
where $\alpha=\tau^{(I)}/\tau_{\perp}^{(P)}$.
